{
  "id": 5068439115923456,
  "name": "Disconnect WebSockets on BFCache entry",
  "summary": "Chrome is changing its behavior to allow pages with active WebSocket connections to enter the Back/Forward Cache. To achieve this, active WebSockets will now be disconnected when a page is cached. Previously, active WebSocket connections prevented pages from entering BFCache.\n\nThe BackForwardCacheForWebSocketsAllowed policy is provided as a temporary escape hatch for enterprises. Setting this policy to Disabled will revert to the previous behavior (preventing pages with active WebSockets from entering BFCache), which will prevent breakage in legacy apps that lack WebSocket reconnection logic.",
